$ Oracle: DBA_PDBS
@ dba_pdbs

? `dba_pdbs` lists all PDBs that belong to a given CDB:
   • In a CDB root: all PDBs of this root
   • An an application root: the PDBs of the application container
   • In a regular PDB or in an application PDB: itself

sa:

 `→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/pdbs`
